searchData={"items":[{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha","doc":"Public facade for the ex_waha library.\n\nExWaha is a provider-agnostic WhatsApp client. Two providers ship in the box:\n\n  * `ExWaha.Providers.Waha` — wraps a self-hosted WAHA server (WhatsApp HTTP API).\n  * `ExWaha.Providers.Meta` — wraps Meta's official WhatsApp Business Cloud API.\n\nBoth implement `ExWaha.Provider`. Application code talks to the facade and\nthe facade dispatches based on the account struct it receives.","ref":"ExWaha.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Multi-tenancy - ExWaha","doc":"ExWaha is stateless and persistence-free. Each call takes an account struct\n(`ExWaha.Providers.Waha.Account` or `ExWaha.Providers.Meta.Account`) and a\nrecipient. Host applications own the mapping `profile_id -> account` in their\ndatabase. See the [Multi-tenancy guide](multi_tenancy.md).","ref":"ExWaha.html#module-multi-tenancy"},{"type":"module","title":"Ban risk - ExWaha","doc":"WhatsApp aggressively bans accounts that look like bots. The OTP layer\n(`ExWaha.Session.Server`) enforces a token-bucket rate limit, a warmup ramp\nfor new sessions, and randomized jitter between sends. Outbound code paths\nshould go through this facade (which calls `ExWaha.SafeSend`) rather than\nthe raw provider modules. See the [Safety and bans guide](safety_and_bans.md).","ref":"ExWaha.html#module-ban-risk"},{"type":"module","title":"Quick examples - ExWaha","doc":"account =\n      ExWaha.Providers.Waha.Account.new(\n        ExWaha.Instance.new(base_url: \"http://localhost:3000\", api_key: \"key\"),\n        \"profile_42\"\n      )\n\n    ExWaha.send_text(account, \"+201001234567\", \"Hello!\")\n    #=> {:ok, %{\"id\" => \"msg_abc\"}}","ref":"ExWaha.html#module-quick-examples"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.account/0","doc":"Either a WAHA or Meta account struct.","ref":"ExWaha.html#t:account/0"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.recipient/0","doc":"An `ExWaha.Recipient` struct or a phone string. Strings get normalized.","ref":"ExWaha.html#t:recipient/0"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.send_media/4","doc":"Send a media message (image, video, audio, document) via the safety gate.\n\nThe `media` map must include `:type` (`:image | :video | :audio | :document`)\nand the provider-specific media descriptor.","ref":"ExWaha.html#send_media/4"},{"type":"function","title":"WAHA example - ExWaha.send_media/4","doc":"ExWaha.send_media(account, \"+201001234567\", %{\n      type: :image,\n      file: %{url: \"https://example.com/photo.jpg\"},\n      caption: \"look at this\"\n    })","ref":"ExWaha.html#send_media/4-waha-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Meta example - ExWaha.send_media/4","doc":"ExWaha.send_media(meta_account, \"+201001234567\", %{\n      type: :image,\n      link: \"https://example.com/photo.jpg\",\n      caption: \"look at this\"\n    })","ref":"ExWaha.html#send_media/4-meta-example"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.send_template/4","doc":"Send a pre-approved Meta message template.\n\nMeta requires templates outside the 24-hour customer service window. WAHA\nreturns `{:error, %ExWaha.Error{reason: :forbidden}}` since it does not\nparticipate in the template system.","ref":"ExWaha.html#send_template/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - ExWaha.send_template/4","doc":"* `:language` — template language code (defaults to `\"en_US\"`)\n  * `:components` — Meta template components list (header / body / button\n    parameters)","ref":"ExWaha.html#send_template/4-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - ExWaha.send_template/4","doc":"ExWaha.send_template(meta_account, \"+201001234567\", \"order_shipped\",\n      language: \"en_US\",\n      components: [\n        %{\n          type: \"body\",\n          parameters: [%{type: \"text\", text: \"TRACK-12345\"}]\n        }\n      ]\n    )","ref":"ExWaha.html#send_template/4-example"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.send_text/4","doc":"Send a text message via the safety gate.\n\nThe recipient can be:\n\n  * a phone string in any format — non-digits are stripped\n  * an `ExWaha.Recipient` struct (see `ExWaha.Recipient.new/1` and\n    `ExWaha.Recipient.group/1`)","ref":"ExWaha.html#send_text/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - ExWaha.send_text/4","doc":"Forwarded to the underlying provider. WAHA accepts `:reply_to` and\n`:link_preview`. Meta accepts `:preview_url`.","ref":"ExWaha.html#send_text/4-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - ExWaha.send_text/4","doc":"* `{:ok, response_body}` on 2xx\n  * `{:error, %ExWaha.Error{}}` on rate-limit refusal, signature failure,\n    transport errors, or non-2xx responses","ref":"ExWaha.html#send_text/4-returns"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - ExWaha.send_text/4","doc":"iex> account = build_account()\n    iex> ExWaha.send_text(account, \"+20 100 123 4567\", \"Hello!\")\n    {:ok, %{\"id\" => \"msg_...\"}}","ref":"ExWaha.html#send_text/4-example"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.SafeSend","doc":"The single gate every outbound message must pass through.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n  1. Locate (or skip) the per-account `ExWaha.Session.Server`.\n  2. Check the rate-limit token bucket.\n  3. Verify the session is in a sendable state.\n  4. Apply randomized jitter (ban-risk mitigation).\n  5. Emit telemetry on throttle and dispatch.\n\nIf no session server is registered for the account (e.g. tests, or an app\nthat hasn't started one), `dispatch/2` falls through to the inner function\nwithout limits — explicit opt-in to safety via the OTP layer.","ref":"ExWaha.SafeSend.html"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.SafeSend.result/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.SafeSend.html#t:result/0"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.SafeSend.dispatch/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.SafeSend.html#dispatch/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.SafeSend.sleep_jitter/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.SafeSend.html#sleep_jitter/1"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Instance","doc":"Configuration for a single WAHA server.\n\nAn `Instance` describes how to reach a WAHA Docker container. Multiple\ninstances coexist — pass the right one per call. No global state.","ref":"ExWaha.Instance.html"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Instance.t/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Instance.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Instance.new/1","doc":"Build an `Instance` from keyword opts.","ref":"ExWaha.Instance.html#new/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Required - ExWaha.Instance.new/1","doc":"* `:base_url` — full URL to the WAHA server (e.g. `\"http://waha:3000\"`)","ref":"ExWaha.Instance.html#new/1-required"},{"type":"function","title":"Optional - ExWaha.Instance.new/1","doc":"* `:api_key` — `X-Api-Key` header value (set if WAHA was started with one)\n  * `:http_client` — module implementing `ExWaha.Client` (defaults to\n    `ExWaha.Client.Req` via application config)\n  * `:timeout_ms` — connect timeout (default `10_000`)\n  * `:receive_timeout_ms` — response timeout (default `30_000`)\n  * `:headers` — additional request headers (default `[]`)","ref":"ExWaha.Instance.html#new/1-optional"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - ExWaha.Instance.new/1","doc":"ExWaha.Instance.new(\n      base_url: \"http://waha.internal:3000\",\n      api_key: System.fetch_env!(\"WAHA_API_KEY\")\n    )","ref":"ExWaha.Instance.html#new/1-example"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Providers.Waha","doc":"Provider implementation for self-hosted WAHA (https://waha.devlike.pro).\n\nAll requests go through the configurable `ExWaha.Client`. The session\nparameter scopes the call to a single WhatsApp account on the WAHA server.","ref":"ExWaha.Providers.Waha.html"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Providers.Waha.Account","doc":"An account on a specific WAHA server.\n\nCombines:\n\n  * `instance` — `%ExWaha.Instance{}` (server connection details)\n  * `session` — WAHA session name, typically derived from your tenant id\n    (e.g. `\"profile_42\"`)\n  * `webhook_secret` — optional HMAC-SHA512 secret WAHA was configured with","ref":"ExWaha.Providers.Waha.Account.html"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Providers.Waha.Account.t/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Providers.Waha.Account.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Providers.Waha.Account.new/3","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Providers.Waha.Account.html#new/3"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Providers.Meta","doc":"Provider implementation for Meta's WhatsApp Business Cloud API.\n\nReference: https://developers.facebook.com/docs/whatsapp/cloud-api\n\nDifferences vs WAHA:\n\n  * Auth is `Authorization: Bearer  `.\n  * Outbound URL is `POST https://graph.facebook.com/ / /messages`.\n  * Free-form messages only allowed inside the 24-hour customer service window.\n    Outside that window you must use a pre-approved `template`.\n  * Webhook signature is `X-Hub-Signature-256: sha256= ` over the raw body\n    using the App Secret.","ref":"ExWaha.Providers.Meta.html"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Providers.Meta.Account","doc":"An account on Meta's WhatsApp Business Cloud API.","ref":"ExWaha.Providers.Meta.Account.html"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Providers.Meta.Account.t/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Providers.Meta.Account.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Providers.Meta.Account.new/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Providers.Meta.Account.html#new/1"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Api.Auth","doc":"Pairing endpoints — QR scan and SMS code request.\n\nWhatsApp authentication happens once per session. Render the QR (or\nrequest a numeric code) to the user, who confirms in the WhatsApp mobile\napp under *Linked Devices*.\n\nAfter a successful pairing, WAHA fires a `session.status` webhook with\nstatus `WORKING`. Update your `ExWaha.Session.Server` accordingly.","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Auth.html"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Auth.qr/2","doc":"Fetch the QR code for the session.","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Auth.html#qr/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - ExWaha.Api.Auth.qr/2","doc":"* `:format` — `:raw` (default) or `:image`\n    - `:raw` returns `{:ok, %{\"value\" => \" \"}}`\n    - `:image` returns the raw PNG bytes (caller decodes)","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Auth.html#qr/2-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Example (LiveView) - ExWaha.Api.Auth.qr/2","doc":"def handle_info(:poll_qr, socket) do\n      case ExWaha.Api.Auth.qr(socket.assigns.account, format: :raw) do\n        {:ok, %{\"value\" => b64}} ->\n          {:noreply, assign(socket, qr: b64)}\n\n        {:error, _} ->\n          Process.send_after(self(), :poll_qr, 2000)\n          {:noreply, socket}\n      end\n    end","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Auth.html#qr/2-example-liveview"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Auth.request_code/2","doc":"Request a numeric pairing code (alternative to QR scanning).\n\nUseful when the user can't easily scan a screen — they enter the returned\ncode in WhatsApp → Linked Devices → Link with phone number instead.\n\n    ExWaha.Api.Auth.request_code(account, \"+201001234567\")\n    #=> {:ok, %{\"code\" => \"ABC1-DEF2\"}}","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Auth.html#request_code/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Auth.screenshot/1","doc":"Take a screenshot of the WhatsApp Web view (debug aid).","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Auth.html#screenshot/1"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Api.Chats","doc":"WAHA chat endpoints.","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Chats.html"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Chats.archive/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Chats.html#archive/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Chats.delete/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Chats.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Chats.list/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Chats.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Chats.messages/3","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Chats.html#messages/3"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Api.Contacts","doc":"WAHA contact endpoints. Use `check_exists/2` BEFORE sending to unknowns.","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Contacts.html"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Contacts.check_exists/2","doc":"Check whether a phone number is registered on WhatsApp.\n\nThis is the single most important call to make before sending unsolicited\noutbound — sending to non-WhatsApp numbers is a strong ban signal.","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Contacts.html#check_exists/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Contacts.get/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Contacts.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Contacts.profile_picture/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Contacts.html#profile_picture/2"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Api.Groups","doc":"WAHA group endpoints.","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Groups.html"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Groups.add_participants/3","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Groups.html#add_participants/3"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Groups.create/3","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Groups.html#create/3"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Groups.get/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Groups.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Groups.leave/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Groups.html#leave/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Groups.list/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Groups.html#list/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Groups.remove_participants/3","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Groups.html#remove_participants/3"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Api.Messages","doc":"Message-sending endpoints for WAHA.\n\nNote: passing through `ExWaha.SafeSend` is strongly recommended over calling\nthese directly — the safe layer enforces rate limits, warmup, and jitter.","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Messages.html"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Messages.send_location/3","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Messages.html#send_location/3"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Messages.send_media/4","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Messages.html#send_media/4"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Messages.send_seen/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Messages.html#send_seen/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Messages.send_text/4","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Messages.html#send_text/4"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Api.Presence","doc":"WAHA presence endpoints.","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Presence.html"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Presence.set/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Presence.html#set/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Presence.start_typing/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Presence.html#start_typing/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Presence.stop_typing/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Presence.html#stop_typing/2"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Api.Profile","doc":"WAHA profile endpoints.","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Profile.html"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Profile.me/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Profile.html#me/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Profile.set_name/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Profile.html#set_name/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Profile.set_status/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Profile.html#set_status/2"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Api.Sessions","doc":"WAHA `/api/sessions` endpoints.\n\nWAHA sessions follow this lifecycle:\n\n    STOPPED ──start──▶ STARTING ──pair──▶ SCAN_QR ──scan──▶ WORKING\n                                                            │\n                                                            └─▶ FAILED\n\nAll functions take an `ExWaha.Providers.Waha.Account` (which carries the\nsession name) and return `{:ok, body} | {:error, %ExWaha.Error{}}`.","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Sessions.html"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Sessions.create/2","doc":"Create the session on WAHA. Idempotent — safe to call repeatedly.\n\nPass `config` to set webhooks, proxy, debug flags, etc. (see WAHA docs).","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Sessions.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - ExWaha.Api.Sessions.create/2","doc":"ExWaha.Api.Sessions.create(account, %{\n      webhooks: [\n        %{\n          url: \"https://api.example.com/webhooks/waha/profile_42\",\n          events: [\"message\", \"session.status\"],\n          hmac: %{key: account.webhook_secret}\n        }\n      ]\n    })","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Sessions.html#create/2-example"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Sessions.get/1","doc":"Fetch the current session by name (from the account).","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Sessions.html#get/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Sessions.list/1","doc":"List all sessions on the WAHA server.","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Sessions.html#list/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - ExWaha.Api.Sessions.list/1","doc":"{:ok, sessions} = ExWaha.Api.Sessions.list(account)\n    Enum.map(sessions, & &1[\"name\"])\n    #=> [\"profile_42\", \"profile_99\"]","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Sessions.html#list/1-example"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Sessions.logout/1","doc":"Log out and unpair the WhatsApp account. Requires re-scanning a QR.","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Sessions.html#logout/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Sessions.restart/1","doc":"Stop then start the session — sometimes needed after long idle periods.","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Sessions.html#restart/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Sessions.start/1","doc":"Start a previously-created (and stopped) session.","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Sessions.html#start/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Api.Sessions.stop/1","doc":"Stop the session (preserves the WhatsApp pairing).","ref":"ExWaha.Api.Sessions.html#stop/1"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Safety.RateLimiter","doc":"Pure token-bucket rate limiter.\n\nThis module is data-only — caller threads the bucket through state. The\nper-session `ExWaha.Session.Server` keeps one bucket per WhatsApp account.\n\nWhy per-account: WhatsApp's rate limits are tracked per phone number, not\nper server. A global limiter would either over-throttle small tenants or\nunder-throttle big ones.","ref":"ExWaha.Safety.RateLimiter.html"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Safety.RateLimiter.t/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Safety.RateLimiter.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Safety.RateLimiter.new/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Safety.RateLimiter.html#new/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Safety.RateLimiter.resize/3","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Safety.RateLimiter.html#resize/3"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Safety.RateLimiter.take/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Safety.RateLimiter.html#take/2"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Safety.Warmup","doc":"Account warmup curve.\n\nWhatsApp's anti-spam systems are most aggressive against new numbers and\nnumbers that suddenly start sending more. A new account should send slowly\nand ramp up over days. This module computes the bucket parameters for a\ngiven account age.","ref":"ExWaha.Safety.Warmup.html"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Safety.Warmup.bucket_params/0","doc":"Bucket parameters: {capacity, refill_per_second}.","ref":"ExWaha.Safety.Warmup.html#t:bucket_params/0"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Safety.Warmup.params/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Safety.Warmup.html#params/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Safety.Warmup.random_jitter_ms/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Safety.Warmup.html#random_jitter_ms/1"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Session.Registry","doc":"Process registry for `ExWaha.Session.Server` instances.\n\nRegistry key is a stable `{provider, account_key}` tuple so the same logical\naccount always resolves to the same server — even across restarts.","ref":"ExWaha.Session.Registry.html"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Session.Registry.key/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Session.Registry.html#key/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Session.Registry.lookup/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Session.Registry.html#lookup/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Session.Registry.via/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Session.Registry.html#via/1"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Session.Server","doc":"Per-account state machine.\n\nHolds:\n\n  * the account struct\n  * status (`:stopped | :starting | :scan_qr | :working | :failed`)\n  * a token-bucket rate limiter (sized by warmup age)\n  * jitter config\n\n`gated_call/2` is the public API used by `ExWaha.SafeSend`. It serializes the\nrate-limit check (so two concurrent senders can't both consume the last\ntoken) but releases the GenServer before performing the HTTP call so the\nprocess is not the bottleneck.","ref":"ExWaha.Session.Server.html"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Session.Server.status/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Session.Server.html#t:status/0"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Session.Server.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"ExWaha.Session.Server.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Session.Server.gated_call/3","doc":"Block until rate limit allows, then run `fun` outside the GenServer.","ref":"ExWaha.Session.Server.html#gated_call/3"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Session.Server.set_status/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Session.Server.html#set_status/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Session.Server.start_link/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Session.Server.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Session.Server.status/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Session.Server.html#status/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Session.Server.subscribe/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Session.Server.html#subscribe/2"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Session.Supervisor","doc":"DynamicSupervisor for per-account `ExWaha.Session.Server` processes.","ref":"ExWaha.Session.Supervisor.html"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Session.Supervisor.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"ExWaha.Session.Supervisor.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Session.Supervisor.ensure_started/2","doc":"Start (or look up) the session server for an account. Idempotent.","ref":"ExWaha.Session.Supervisor.html#ensure_started/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Session.Supervisor.start_link/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Session.Supervisor.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Session.Supervisor.stop/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Session.Supervisor.html#stop/1"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Event","doc":"Normalized webhook event.\n\nWAHA and Meta send wildly different payloads — this struct is the lowest\ncommon denominator that downstream code (handlers, LiveViews, Oban jobs)\nworks with. The raw provider payload is preserved for advanced cases.","ref":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Event.html"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Event.kind/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Event.html#t:kind/0"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Event.t/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Event.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Event.from_meta/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Event.html#from_meta/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Event.from_waha/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Event.html#from_waha/1"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Handler","doc":"Behaviour host applications implement to receive normalized events.\n\nMount the host's handler module via `ExWahaPhoenix.WebhookPlug` (Phoenix\napps) or call `ExWaha.Webhooks.Handler.dispatch/3` directly from a custom\ntransport.","ref":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Handler.html"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"Example - ExWaha.Webhooks.Handler","doc":"defmodule MyApp.WhatsappHandler do\n      @behaviour ExWaha.Webhooks.Handler\n\n      def handle_event(%ExWaha.Webhooks.Event{kind: :message} = event, ctx) do\n        MyApp.Whatsapp.persist_inbound(event, ctx)\n        :ok\n      end\n\n      def handle_event(_event, _ctx), do: :ok\n    end","ref":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Handler.html#module-example"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Handler.context/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Handler.html#t:context/0"},{"type":"callback","title":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Handler.handle_event/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Handler.html#c:handle_event/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Handler.dispatch/3","doc":"Run the handler for each event with telemetry around it.","ref":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Handler.html#dispatch/3"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Signature","doc":"HMAC signature verification for webhook payloads.\n\n  * WAHA — `HMAC-SHA512(body, secret)` hex digest in the `X-Webhook-Hmac` header.\n  * Meta — `sha256=` + `HMAC-SHA256(body, app_secret)` hex digest in the\n    `X-Hub-Signature-256` header.\n\nConstant-time comparison via `:crypto.hash_equals/2` to prevent timing\nattacks. Raw request body must be preserved (Plug strips it by default —\nuse a `body_reader` to capture).","ref":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Signature.html"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Signature.verify_meta_sha256/3","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Signature.html#verify_meta_sha256/3"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Signature.verify_sha512/3","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Webhooks.Signature.html#verify_sha512/3"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"ExWaha.Client","doc":"HTTP client behaviour. Implementations: `ExWaha.Client.Req` (default) and\n`ExWaha.ClientMock` (test only).\n\nDesigned so all transport concerns are a single mockable seam.","ref":"ExWaha.Client.html"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Client.body/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Client.html#t:body/0"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Client.error/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Client.html#t:error/0"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Client.headers/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Client.html#t:headers/0"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Client.method/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Client.html#t:method/0"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Client.opts/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Client.html#t:opts/0"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Client.response/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Client.html#t:response/0"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Client.url/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Client.html#t:url/0"},{"type":"callback","title":"ExWaha.Client.request/5","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Client.html#c:request/5"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Client.impl/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Client.html#impl/0"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Client.request/5","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Client.html#request/5"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"ExWaha.Provider","doc":"Behaviour every WhatsApp provider implements.\n\nThe facade (`ExWaha`) dispatches by inspecting the account struct's module's\n`provider/0` callback (set via `use ExWaha.Provider, ...`) — but in practice\nwe keep it explicit by pattern-matching on the account struct in `dispatch/2`.","ref":"ExWaha.Provider.html"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Provider.account/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Provider.html#t:account/0"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Provider.recipient/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Provider.html#t:recipient/0"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Provider.result/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Provider.html#t:result/1"},{"type":"callback","title":"ExWaha.Provider.parse_event/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Provider.html#c:parse_event/2"},{"type":"callback","title":"ExWaha.Provider.send_media/4","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Provider.html#c:send_media/4"},{"type":"callback","title":"ExWaha.Provider.send_template/4","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Provider.html#c:send_template/4"},{"type":"callback","title":"ExWaha.Provider.send_text/4","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Provider.html#c:send_text/4"},{"type":"callback","title":"ExWaha.Provider.verify_signature/3","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Provider.html#c:verify_signature/3"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Provider.provider_for!/1","doc":"Look up the provider module for an account struct.","ref":"ExWaha.Provider.html#provider_for!/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Provider.send_media/4","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Provider.html#send_media/4"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Provider.send_template/4","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Provider.html#send_template/4"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Provider.send_text/4","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Provider.html#send_text/4"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Client.Req","doc":"Default `ExWaha.Client` implementation backed by `Req`.\n\nReturns `{:ok, response}` on any HTTP response (caller maps status to error)\nand `{:error, %ExWaha.Error{}}` on transport failures.","ref":"ExWaha.Client.Req.html"},{"type":"exception","title":"ExWaha.Error","doc":"Normalized error returned by every ExWaha call.\n\nReasons:\n\n  * `:rate_limited` — local token bucket refused the call (back off and retry).\n  * `:session_not_started` — provider session is not in a sendable state.\n  * `:invalid_recipient` — recipient is not on WhatsApp or wrong format.\n  * `:unauthorized` — bad API key / access token.\n  * `:forbidden` — likely policy violation (template required, 24h window).\n  * `:account_banned` — provider says this number is banned.\n  * `:network` — transport failure (timeout, DNS, etc.).\n  * `:server_error` — provider returned 5xx.\n  * `:unknown` — fallback.","ref":"ExWaha.Error.html"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Error.reason/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Error.html#t:reason/0"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Error.t/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Error.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Error.from_status/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Error.html#from_status/2"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Recipient","doc":"Normalized recipient handle.\n\nDifferent providers expect different chat-id formats. This struct captures the\ncanonical phone number plus an optional WAHA-style chat id, and provides\nhelpers to render the right shape per provider.\n\nWAHA expects ` @c.us` for users and ` @g.us` for groups. Meta Cloud\nAPI expects E.164 digits without `+`.","ref":"ExWaha.Recipient.html"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWaha.Recipient.t/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Recipient.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Recipient.group/1","doc":"Build a group `Recipient` from a WAHA group id.\n\n    iex> ExWaha.Recipient.group(\"123-456\")\n    %ExWaha.Recipient{phone: \"123-456\", chat_id: \"123-456@g.us\", type: :group}","ref":"ExWaha.Recipient.html#group/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Recipient.new/1","doc":"Build a user `Recipient` from a phone string. Non-digits are stripped.\n\n    iex> ExWaha.Recipient.new(\"+20 (100) 123-4567\")\n    %ExWaha.Recipient{phone: \"201001234567\", chat_id: \"201001234567@c.us\", type: :user}\n\nAlready-built `Recipient` structs pass through unchanged.","ref":"ExWaha.Recipient.html#new/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Recipient.to_meta/1","doc":"Render the recipient as plain digits for the Meta Cloud API.","ref":"ExWaha.Recipient.html#to_meta/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Recipient.to_waha/1","doc":"Render the recipient in WAHA's ` @c.us` / ` @g.us` format.","ref":"ExWaha.Recipient.html#to_waha/1"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWaha.Telemetry","doc":"Telemetry event names emitted by ex_waha.\n\nStandard span events (`:start`, `:stop`, `:exception`) are emitted for every\noutbound call. Subscribe via `:telemetry.attach/4`.\n\nEvents:\n\n  * `[:ex_waha, :request, :start | :stop | :exception]`\n  * `[:ex_waha, :webhook, :received]`\n  * `[:ex_waha, :rate_limit, :throttled]`\n  * `[:ex_waha, :session, :status_changed]`","ref":"ExWaha.Telemetry.html"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Telemetry.emit/3","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Telemetry.html#emit/3"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWaha.Telemetry.span/3","doc":"","ref":"ExWaha.Telemetry.html#span/3"},{"type":"extras","title":"ExWaha","doc":"# ExWaha\n\n[![Hex.pm](https://img.shields.io/hexpm/v/ex_waha.svg)](https://hex.pm/packages/ex_waha)\n[![Documentation](https://img.shields.io/badge/hex-docs-lightgreen.svg)](https://hexdocs.pm/ex_waha)\n\nProvider-agnostic WhatsApp client for Elixir. Talk to a self-hosted [WAHA](https://waha.devlike.pro)\nserver **or** Meta's official WhatsApp Business Cloud API through the same\nfunction calls. Multi-tenant by construction. Ban-aware by default.\n\n> **Heads up:** Sending WhatsApp messages — especially via WAHA, which uses the\n> WhatsApp Web protocol — carries real risk of account bans. Read\n> [Safety and bans](guides/safety_and_bans.md) before going to production.","ref":"readme.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Installation - ExWaha","doc":"Add `:ex_waha` to your `mix.exs`:\n\n```elixir\ndef deps do\n  [\n    {:ex_waha, \"~> 0.1.0\"}\n  ]\nend\n```\n\nIf you'll receive webhooks via Phoenix, also add\n[`:ex_waha_phoenix`](https://hex.pm/packages/ex_waha_phoenix). If you use Ash,\nadd [`:ash_waha`](https://hex.pm/packages/ash_waha).","ref":"readme.html#installation"},{"type":"extras","title":"Quick start - ExWaha","doc":"```elixir\n# 1. Build a per-tenant account struct\naccount =\n  ExWaha.Providers.Waha.Account.new(\n    ExWaha.Instance.new(\n      base_url: \"http://waha.internal:3000\",\n      api_key: System.fetch_env!(\"WAHA_API_KEY\")\n    ),\n    \"profile_42\",                       # session name (your tenant id, derived)\n    webhook_secret: System.fetch_env!(\"WAHA_WEBHOOK_SECRET\")\n  )\n\n# 2. Bring it under the safety supervisor (rate limit + warmup + jitter)\n{:ok, _pid} = ExWaha.Session.Supervisor.ensure_started(account)\n\n# 3. After WAHA reports the WhatsApp pairing succeeded, mark it sendable\nExWaha.Session.Server.set_status(\n  ExWaha.Session.Registry.via(account),\n  :working\n)\n\n# 4. Send messages through the safe gate\n{:ok, _resp} = ExWaha.send_text(account, \"+20 100 123 4567\", \"Hi!\")\n```","ref":"readme.html#quick-start"},{"type":"extras","title":"Architecture - ExWaha","doc":"```\n                       ExWaha (facade)\n                            │\n                       SafeSend (gate)\n                       │           │\n        Session.Server (per acct)  └──── (no server: bypass)\n        ├ token bucket\n        ├ warmup curve\n        ├ jitter\n        └ status state\n                            │\n                    Provider (behaviour)\n                  ┌─────────┴──────────┐\n        Providers.Waha           Providers.Meta\n              │                          │\n        Api.* modules              Cloud API calls\n              │                          │\n                  Client (behaviour)\n                  ├ Client.Req (default)\n                  └ ClientMock  (test)\n```\n\nThe OTP layer is **opt-in**. Calls without a registered `Session.Server`\nfall through to the raw HTTP client, useful for tests and one-off scripts.","ref":"readme.html#architecture"},{"type":"extras","title":"Two providers, one API - ExWaha","doc":"```elixir\n# Self-hosted WAHA\nwaha = ExWaha.Providers.Waha.Account.new(instance, \"profile_42\")\nExWaha.send_text(waha, \"+201001234567\", \"via WAHA\")\n\n# Meta Cloud API\nmeta =\n  ExWaha.Providers.Meta.Account.new(\n    phone_number_id: System.fetch_env!(\"META_PHONE_NUMBER_ID\"),\n    access_token:    System.fetch_env!(\"META_ACCESS_TOKEN\"),\n    app_secret:      System.fetch_env!(\"META_APP_SECRET\")\n  )\n\nExWaha.send_text(meta, \"+201001234567\", \"via Meta\")\nExWaha.send_template(meta, \"+201001234567\", \"hello_world\", language: \"en_US\")\n```","ref":"readme.html#two-providers-one-api"},{"type":"extras","title":"Multi-tenancy - ExWaha","doc":"ExWaha owns no persistence. Your application maps `profile_id` → account in\nits own database. The recommended convention is a deterministic session name:\n\n```elixir\ndefmodule MyApp.Whatsapp do\n  alias ExWaha.{Instance, Providers.Waha.Account}\n\n  def account_for(profile_id) do\n    Account.new(\n      Instance.new(base_url: waha_base_url(), api_key: waha_api_key()),\n      \"profile_#{profile_id}\",\n      webhook_secret: waha_webhook_secret()\n    )\n  end\nend\n```\n\nFor per-tenant WAHA instances (different servers per customer), look up the\nURL/key from your `instances` table inside `account_for/1`.\n\nSee [Multi-tenancy guide](guides/multi_tenancy.md).","ref":"readme.html#multi-tenancy"},{"type":"extras","title":"Receiving webhooks - ExWaha","doc":"If you're on Phoenix, use [`ExWahaPhoenix.WebhookPlug`](https://hexdocs.pm/ex_waha_phoenix).\nFor other transports, call `ExWaha.Webhooks.Handler.dispatch/3` from your\ncontroller.\n\n```elixir\ndefmodule MyApp.Whatsapp.Handler do\n  @behaviour ExWaha.Webhooks.Handler\n\n  def handle_event(%ExWaha.Webhooks.Event{kind: :message} = event, ctx) do\n    Phoenix.PubSub.broadcast(\n      MyApp.PubSub,\n      \"whatsapp:#{ctx.account.session}\",\n      {:waha_message, event}\n    )\n    :ok\n  end\n\n  def handle_event(_, _ctx), do: :ok\nend\n```\n\nSee [Webhooks guide](guides/webhooks.md).","ref":"readme.html#receiving-webhooks"},{"type":"extras","title":"Telemetry - ExWaha","doc":"Every outbound call is wrapped in a `:telemetry.span/3`. Subscribe with the\nstandard machinery — no per-app integration needed.\n\n```elixir\n:telemetry.attach_many(\n  \"ex-waha-logger\",\n  [\n    [:ex_waha, :request, :stop],\n    [:ex_waha, :rate_limit, :throttled],\n    [:ex_waha, :session, :status_changed]\n  ],\n  &MyApp.Telemetry.handle_event/4,\n  nil\n)\n```\n\nSee [Telemetry events](guides/telemetry.md) for the full list.","ref":"readme.html#telemetry"},{"type":"extras","title":"Documentation - ExWaha","doc":"- [Getting started](guides/getting_started.md)\n- [Multi-tenancy](guides/multi_tenancy.md)\n- [Safety and bans](guides/safety_and_bans.md)\n- [Webhooks](guides/webhooks.md)\n- [Providers (WAHA & Meta)](guides/providers.md)\n- [Telemetry events](guides/telemetry.md)","ref":"readme.html#documentation"},{"type":"extras","title":"License - ExWaha","doc":"MIT. See the LICENSE file included in the package.","ref":"readme.html#license"},{"type":"extras","title":"Changelog","doc":"# Changelog\n\nAll notable changes to `:ex_waha` will be documented here. The format follows\n[Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/) and the project adheres to\n[Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/).\n\n## [Unreleased]\n\n## [0.1.0] - 2026-04-27","ref":"changelog.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Added - Changelog","doc":"- Provider-agnostic facade (`ExWaha`) with `send_text/4`, `send_media/4`,\n  `send_template/4`.\n- `ExWaha.Provider` behaviour with WAHA and Meta Cloud API implementations.\n- Configurable HTTP transport via `ExWaha.Client` behaviour with a\n  `Req`-backed default and a Mox-friendly seam for tests.\n- Per-account OTP layer: `Session.Registry`, `Session.Supervisor`,\n  `Session.Server` with token-bucket rate limiting, warmup ramp, and\n  randomized jitter.\n- Webhook subsystem: normalized `Event` struct for both providers, HMAC\n  signature verification (SHA-512 for WAHA, SHA-256 for Meta), and a\n  pluggable `Handler` behaviour.\n- WAHA REST API surface: `Sessions`, `Auth`, `Messages`, `Chats`, `Contacts`,\n  `Groups`, `Presence`, `Profile`.\n- Telemetry spans on every request plus discrete events for throttle and\n  status changes.","ref":"changelog.html#added"},{"type":"extras","title":"Getting started","doc":"# Getting started\n\nThis guide walks through setting up `:ex_waha` end to end with a self-hosted\nWAHA server and sending the first message.\n\nIf you only want the official Meta Cloud API, skip to the\n[Providers guide](providers.md) — the WAHA-specific setup steps don't apply.","ref":"getting_started.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"1. Run a WAHA server - Getting started","doc":"WAHA ships as a Docker image. The simplest dev setup:\n\n```bash\ndocker run -it --rm \\\n  -p 3000:3000 \\\n  -e WAHA_API_KEY=dev_key \\\n  -e WHATSAPP_HOOK_URL=http://host.docker.internal:4000/webhooks/waha/local \\\n  -e WHATSAPP_HOOK_HMAC_KEY=dev_secret \\\n  devlikeapro/waha\n```\n\nOpen `http://localhost:3000/dashboard` to confirm it's running.","ref":"getting_started.html#1-run-a-waha-server"},{"type":"extras","title":"2. Add the dependency - Getting started","doc":"```elixir\n# mix.exs\ndef deps do\n  [\n    {:ex_waha, \"~> 0.1.0\"}\n  ]\nend\n```\n\n`:ex_waha` starts its own application — `Application.start/2` boots a\n`Registry` and the per-account `DynamicSupervisor`. You don't need to add\nanything to your supervision tree.","ref":"getting_started.html#2-add-the-dependency"},{"type":"extras","title":"3. Build an account - Getting started","doc":"A `%ExWaha.Providers.Waha.Account{}` packages the server connection details\n(`%ExWaha.Instance{}`) plus the per-tenant session name:\n\n```elixir\ninstance =\n  ExWaha.Instance.new(\n    base_url: \"http://localhost:3000\",\n    api_key: \"dev_key\"\n  )\n\naccount =\n  ExWaha.Providers.Waha.Account.new(\n    instance,\n    \"profile_42\",\n    webhook_secret: \"dev_secret\"\n  )\n```\n\nThe session name is your tenancy primitive — pick a deterministic scheme\nlike `\"profile_ \"` so you never need a DB lookup to derive it.","ref":"getting_started.html#3-build-an-account"},{"type":"extras","title":"4. Pair the WhatsApp account - Getting started","doc":"WAHA needs to log in to WhatsApp once via QR code:\n\n```elixir\n# Create the session in WAHA (idempotent — safe to call repeatedly)\n{:ok, _} = ExWaha.Api.Sessions.create(account)\n\n# Poll for QR — returns a base64 PNG (or :image format for raw bytes)\n{:ok, %{\"value\" => qr_b64}} = ExWaha.Api.Auth.qr(account, format: :raw)\n```\n\nRender the `qr_b64` value to the user (LiveView or any HTML), and have them\nscan it with WhatsApp → Linked Devices.\n\nWhen pairing succeeds, WAHA fires a `session.status` webhook with status\n`WORKING`.","ref":"getting_started.html#4-pair-the-whatsapp-account"},{"type":"extras","title":"5. Bring the account under safety supervision - Getting started","doc":"The OTP layer enforces rate limits, warmup ramping, and randomized jitter —\nall critical for not getting banned.\n\n```elixir\n{:ok, _pid} = ExWaha.Session.Supervisor.ensure_started(account)\n\n# After WAHA reports paired/working:\nExWaha.Session.Server.set_status(\n  ExWaha.Session.Registry.via(account),\n  :working\n)\n```\n\n`ensure_started/1` is idempotent — safe to call from a controller before\neach send if you don't want to wire it into a startup hook.","ref":"getting_started.html#5-bring-the-account-under-safety-supervision"},{"type":"extras","title":"6. Send - Getting started","doc":"```elixir\n{:ok, _resp} = ExWaha.send_text(account, \"+20 100 123 4567\", \"Hello!\")\n```\n\nThe recipient can be:\n- a phone string (any format — `Recipient.new/1` strips non-digits)\n- a `%ExWaha.Recipient{}` struct (use `Recipient.group/1` for groups)","ref":"getting_started.html#6-send"},{"type":"extras","title":"7. Receive webhooks - Getting started","doc":"If you're on Phoenix, see the [`:ex_waha_phoenix`](https://hexdocs.pm/ex_waha_phoenix)\ndocs.\n\nFor raw Plug/Bandit, the pattern is:\n\n```elixir\ndef handle_webhook(conn, _params) do\n  {:ok, body, conn} = Plug.Conn.read_body(conn)\n  account = lookup_account(conn.path_params[\"session\"])\n\n  with true <- ExWaha.Providers.Waha.verify_signature(account, body, conn.req_headers),\n       {:ok, payload} <- Jason.decode(body),\n       {:ok, events} <- ExWaha.Providers.Waha.parse_event(account, payload) do\n    ExWaha.Webhooks.Handler.dispatch(MyApp.Handler, events, %{account: account})\n    Plug.Conn.send_resp(conn, 200, \"ok\")\n  else\n    false -> Plug.Conn.send_resp(conn, 401, \"\")\n    _ -> Plug.Conn.send_resp(conn, 400, \"\")\n  end\nend\n```","ref":"getting_started.html#7-receive-webhooks"},{"type":"extras","title":"What's next - Getting started","doc":"- [Multi-tenancy guide](multi_tenancy.md) — modeling `profile_id` ↔\n  `instance_id` ↔ session.\n- [Safety and bans](safety_and_bans.md) — what the OTP layer protects you\n  from and what it can't.\n- [Webhooks](webhooks.md) — event shapes for both providers.\n- [Telemetry](telemetry.md) — every event ExWaha emits.","ref":"getting_started.html#what-s-next"},{"type":"extras","title":"Multi-tenancy","doc":"# Multi-tenancy\n\nExWaha owns no persistence and reads no application config inside the call\npath. Every function takes an account struct as the first argument, which\nmakes it natively multi-tenant — but you have to model the mapping yourself.","ref":"multi_tenancy.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Two axes of tenancy - Multi-tenancy","doc":"```\nTenant axis            ExWaha primitive            Where it lives\n─────────────────────  ─────────────────────────  ────────────────────\nInfrastructure         %ExWaha.Instance{}          your `instances` table\n                       (base_url + api_key)\n                       — one WAHA server\n\nAccount / business     session name                derived from profile_id\n                       (string per WhatsApp #)\n```\n\nYou may have a single shared WAHA server hosting many sessions (cheaper,\nsingle point of failure) **or** one WAHA per tenant (isolation, costlier).\nThe same `%Account{}` shape supports both.","ref":"multi_tenancy.html#two-axes-of-tenancy"},{"type":"extras","title":"Recommended schema - Multi-tenancy","doc":"```elixir\ndefmodule MyApp.Repo.Migrations.CreateWhatsappTables do\n  use Ecto.Migration\n\n  def change do\n    create table(:waha_instances, primary_key: false) do\n      add :id, :uuid, primary_key: true\n      add :name, :string, null: false                 # \"shared\", \"customer-acme\"\n      add :base_url, :string, null: false\n      add :api_key, :string, null: false              # encrypted at rest\n      add :webhook_secret, :string, null: false\n      timestamps()\n    end\n\n    create table(:whatsapp_sessions) do\n      add :profile_id, references(:profiles, type: :uuid), null: false\n      add :instance_id, references(:waha_instances, type: :uuid), null: false\n      add :session_name, :string, null: false         # \"profile_ \"\n      add :status, :string, default: \"stopped\"        # mirrors WAHA's enum\n      add :phone_number, :string\n      add :paired_at, :utc_datetime\n      add :last_status_at, :utc_datetime\n      timestamps()\n    end\n\n    create unique_index(:whatsapp_sessions, [:instance_id, :session_name])\n    create unique_index(:whatsapp_sessions, [:profile_id])\n  end\nend\n```","ref":"multi_tenancy.html#recommended-schema"},{"type":"extras","title":"A context module that returns the right account - Multi-tenancy","doc":"```elixir\ndefmodule MyApp.Whatsapp do\n  alias ExWaha.{Instance, Providers.Waha.Account}\n  alias MyApp.Repo\n\n  def account_for!(profile_id) do\n    session = Repo.get_by!(MyApp.Whatsapp.Session, profile_id: profile_id)\n    instance = Repo.get!(MyApp.Whatsapp.Instance, session.instance_id)\n\n    Account.new(\n      Instance.new(base_url: instance.base_url, api_key: instance.api_key),\n      session.session_name,\n      webhook_secret: instance.webhook_secret\n    )\n  end\nend\n```\n\nEvery controller, LiveView, Oban worker, and Ash action that wants to send a\nWhatsApp message goes through this single function. **Never derive the\naccount from URL params** — always from the *current authenticated user's*\nprofile, or you risk one tenant sending as another.","ref":"multi_tenancy.html#a-context-module-that-returns-the-right-account"},{"type":"extras","title":"Authorization rule of thumb - Multi-tenancy","doc":"```elixir\ndefmodule MyAppWeb.WhatsappController do\n  def send(conn, %{\"text\" => text, \"to\" => to}) do\n    profile = conn.assigns.current_user.profile          # <-- from session\n    account = MyApp.Whatsapp.account_for!(profile.id)    # <-- not from params\n\n    case ExWaha.send_text(account, to, text) do\n      {:ok, _} -> json(conn, %{ok: true})\n      {:error, %ExWaha.Error{reason: r}} -> conn |> put_status(422) |> json(%{error: r})\n    end\n  end\nend\n```","ref":"multi_tenancy.html#authorization-rule-of-thumb"},{"type":"extras","title":"Routing webhooks back to a tenant - Multi-tenancy","doc":"When WAHA fires a webhook, the URL must encode enough to look up the right\naccount. Two common patterns:\n\n1. **Per-tenant URL path**: `/webhooks/waha/:profile_id` — `WebhookPlug`\n   resolves the account from the path param.\n2. **Per-instance + session in body**: `/webhooks/waha/:instance_id` —\n   resolve to the right session using `payload[\"session\"]`.\n\nPattern (1) is simpler if you have one WAHA serving everyone. Pattern (2)\nfits when WAHA hosts many sessions per server.\n\n```elixir\n# pattern (1)\nforward \"/webhooks/waha/:profile_id\",\n        ExWahaPhoenix.WebhookPlug,\n        handler: MyApp.Whatsapp.Handler,\n        account: fn conn -> MyApp.Whatsapp.account_for!(conn.path_params[\"profile_id\"]) end\n```","ref":"multi_tenancy.html#routing-webhooks-back-to-a-tenant"},{"type":"extras","title":"Bringing sessions under supervision at startup - Multi-tenancy","doc":"If you want every active session running its safety GenServer immediately\nafter boot (instead of lazily on first send):\n\n```elixir\ndefmodule MyApp.Whatsapp.Bootstrapper do\n  use Task, restart: :transient\n\n  def start_link(_), do: Task.start_link(__MODULE__, :run, [])\n\n  def run do\n    MyApp.Whatsapp.list_active_sessions()\n    |> Enum.each(fn session ->\n      account = MyApp.Whatsapp.account_for!(session.profile_id)\n      {:ok, pid} = ExWaha.Session.Supervisor.ensure_started(account)\n      ExWaha.Session.Server.set_status(pid, status_atom(session.status))\n    end)\n  end\n\n  defp status_atom(\"WORKING\"), do: :working\n  defp status_atom(_), do: :stopped\nend\n```\n\nAdd `MyApp.Whatsapp.Bootstrapper` to your `Application` children, after the\nRepo. Skip it if you'd rather have lazy registration on first call.","ref":"multi_tenancy.html#bringing-sessions-under-supervision-at-startup"},{"type":"extras","title":"Safety and bans","doc":"# Safety and bans\n\nWhatsApp aggressively bans accounts that look automated. This is *not*\noptional reading — getting banned at scale is the single biggest risk of\nrunning on WAHA, and most defenses must be present *before* the first\nmessage goes out. Meta's official Cloud API is friendlier but enforces\ntemplates and the 24-hour customer service window instead.","ref":"safety_and_bans.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"What gets you banned - Safety and bans","doc":"| Signal | Risk | Mitigation built in |\n|---|---|---|\n| Bursty sends from a new number | **Very high** | Warmup curve in `Safety.Warmup` |\n| Sending faster than a human types | High | Token bucket + jitter |\n| Sending to non-WhatsApp numbers | High | `Api.Contacts.check_exists/2` before send |\n| Recipient reports as spam | High | App-level: opt-in tracking, allow unsubscribe |\n| Same number on multiple \"devices\" simultaneously | Medium | One WAHA session per number; don't share |\n| Identical message body to many recipients | Medium | App-level: vary content, use templates on Meta |\n| Sending outside business hours / time zones | Low–Medium | App-level: schedule sends respecting recipient TZ |","ref":"safety_and_bans.html#what-gets-you-banned"},{"type":"extras","title":"What :ex_waha does for you - Safety and bans","doc":"Every send routed through `ExWaha.send_text/4` (or `send_media`,\n`send_template`) goes through `ExWaha.SafeSend.dispatch/2`, which:\n\n1. Looks up the account's `Session.Server` in the registry.\n2. Calls `gated_call/2` which serializes a token-bucket reservation.\n3. If no token is available, returns `{:error, %Error{reason: :rate_limited, retry_after_ms: n}}`.\n4. If the session isn't `:working`, returns `{:error, %Error{reason: :session_not_started}}`.\n5. Otherwise sleeps a randomized jitter (default 300–1500ms) before\n   making the HTTP call.\n\nIf no `Session.Server` is registered for the account, `dispatch/2` falls\nthrough to the bare HTTP call — **explicit opt-out for tests and scripts**.\nIn production code paths, always run sessions under\n`ExWaha.Session.Supervisor`.","ref":"safety_and_bans.html#what-ex_waha-does-for-you"},{"type":"extras","title":"The warmup curve - Safety and bans","doc":"`ExWaha.Safety.Warmup.params/2` interpolates the bucket size and refill\nrate from \"warmup\" defaults to \"steady-state\" defaults over `:warmup_days`\ndays (default 14):\n\n| Day | Capacity | Refill (msg/s) | Effective steady throughput |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 0 | 5 | 0.2 | ~12 msg/min |\n| 7 | 18 | 0.6 | ~36 msg/min |\n| 14+ | 30 | 1.0 | ~60 msg/min |\n\nThese are **conservative** defaults intended to avoid bans on personal\nWhatsApp numbers. Business API numbers tolerate more; tune with:\n\n```elixir\n# config/runtime.exs\nconfig :ex_waha, :rate_limit,\n  capacity: 60,\n  refill_per_second: 2.0,\n  warmup_days: 7,\n  warmup_capacity: 10,\n  warmup_refill_per_second: 0.5,\n  jitter_ms: {500, 2500}\n```\n\nThese are read once when each `Session.Server` initializes. To change the\nbucket on a running session, restart it (terminate + ensure_started).","ref":"safety_and_bans.html#the-warmup-curve"},{"type":"extras","title":"Number existence checks - Safety and bans","doc":"Sending to a number that isn't on WhatsApp is one of the strongest ban\nsignals. For any unsolicited outbound:\n\n```elixir\ncase ExWaha.Api.Contacts.check_exists(account, phone) do\n  {:ok, %{exists: true, chat_id: chat_id}} ->\n    ExWaha.send_text(account, chat_id, text)\n\n  {:ok, %{exists: false}} ->\n    {:error, :not_on_whatsapp}\n\n  {:error, _} = err ->\n    err\nend\n```\n\nBuild this into your enqueue path so the check happens once per recipient\nper day (cache it), not on every message.","ref":"safety_and_bans.html#number-existence-checks"},{"type":"extras","title":"Things ExWaha cannot do for you - Safety and bans","doc":"- **Consent tracking.** Persist explicit opt-in; reject sends to recipients\n  who haven't opted in. Honor \"STOP\" replies.\n- **Business hours.** Don't ping customers at 3am their local time.\n- **Content variation.** Send 1000 identical messages and you will get\n  banned regardless of rate limit.\n- **Quiet days.** Long pauses then bursts look unnatural; spread sends out.\n- **Recovery from ban.** If a session fails repeatedly, *stop sending from\n  that account*. Continued sends after a ban accelerate further action.","ref":"safety_and_bans.html#things-exwaha-cannot-do-for-you"},{"type":"extras","title":"Detecting trouble - Safety and bans","doc":"Monitor these telemetry events:\n\n```elixir\n:telemetry.attach_many(\n  \"ex-waha-bans\",\n  [\n    [:ex_waha, :rate_limit, :throttled],\n    [:ex_waha, :session, :status_changed],\n    [:ex_waha, :request, :stop]\n  ],\n  &MyApp.WhatsappAlerts.handle/4,\n  nil\n)\n```\n\nSpecifically alert on:\n- `request.stop` with `error.reason in [:account_banned, :forbidden]`\n- `session.status_changed` to `:failed` (especially if it bounces repeatedly)\n- A spike in `rate_limit.throttled` (your senders are racing the bucket;\n  raise capacity or reduce send pressure upstream)\n\nWhen in doubt, **stop sending and investigate**. There is no \"unblock\"\nbutton at WhatsApp.","ref":"safety_and_bans.html#detecting-trouble"},{"type":"extras","title":"Webhooks","doc":"# Webhooks\n\nExWaha normalizes the wildly different webhook payload shapes from WAHA\nand Meta into a single `%ExWaha.Webhooks.Event{}` struct that your\napplication code consumes.","ref":"webhooks.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Pipeline - Webhooks","doc":"```\nHTTP POST → verify HMAC → JSON decode → parse_event → handler.handle_event/2\n            (Signature)                  (Provider)    (your module)\n```\n\nIf you're on Phoenix, [`ExWahaPhoenix.WebhookPlug`](https://hexdocs.pm/ex_waha_phoenix)\nruns that whole pipeline for you. For other transports, do it manually.","ref":"webhooks.html#pipeline"},{"type":"extras","title":"Implementing a handler - Webhooks","doc":"```elixir\ndefmodule MyApp.Whatsapp.Handler do\n  @behaviour ExWaha.Webhooks.Handler\n\n  alias ExWaha.Webhooks.Event\n\n  def handle_event(%Event{kind: :message} = e, ctx) do\n    MyApp.Whatsapp.persist_inbound(e, ctx.account)\n    Phoenix.PubSub.broadcast(MyApp.PubSub, \"wa:#{ctx.account.session}\", {:msg, e})\n    :ok\n  end\n\n  def handle_event(%Event{kind: :message_ack} = e, _ctx) do\n    MyApp.Whatsapp.update_delivery_state(e.raw[\"id\"], e.ack_status)\n  end\n\n  def handle_event(%Event{kind: :session_status, raw: raw}, ctx) do\n    new = String.downcase(raw[\"status\"]) |> String.to_existing_atom()\n    pid = ExWaha.Session.Registry.via(ctx.account)\n    ExWaha.Session.Server.set_status(pid, new)\n  end\n\n  def handle_event(_event, _ctx), do: :ok\nend\n```\n\nThe handler runs synchronously inside the webhook request. **Don't do slow\nwork here** — push to Oban / Task.Supervisor for anything beyond a DB write\nor PubSub broadcast.","ref":"webhooks.html#implementing-a-handler"},{"type":"extras","title":"Event reference - Webhooks","doc":"`%ExWaha.Webhooks.Event{}` fields:\n\n| Field | Type | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `provider` | `:waha \\| :meta` | |\n| `kind` | `:message \\| :message_ack \\| :message_reaction \\| :session_status \\| :group_update \\| :presence \\| :unknown` | Normalized across providers |\n| `session` | `String.t() \\| nil` | WAHA session name; nil for Meta |\n| `timestamp` | `DateTime.t() \\| nil` | |\n| `from` | `String.t() \\| nil` | Chat id (`...@c.us`) for WAHA, E.164 for Meta |\n| `to` | `String.t() \\| nil` | |\n| `chat_id` | `String.t() \\| nil` | WAHA only |\n| `body` | `String.t() \\| nil` | Text body for `:message` kind |\n| `media` | `map() \\| nil` | Media descriptor (when present) |\n| `ack_status` | `atom() \\| String.t() \\| nil` | `:sent \\| :delivered \\| :read \\| :played` (or string from Meta) |\n| `raw` | `map()` | Full provider payload — fall back here for fields the normalized form doesn't expose |","ref":"webhooks.html#event-reference"},{"type":"extras","title":"HMAC signatures - Webhooks","doc":"Both providers sign the **raw request body**. If your stack runs `Plug.Parsers`\nbefore signature verification, the body is gone — use the body reader from\n`ExWahaPhoenix.WebhookPlug` (or capture it manually).\n\n| Provider | Algorithm | Header | Format |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| WAHA | HMAC-SHA512 | `X-Webhook-Hmac` | hex digest |\n| Meta | HMAC-SHA256 | `X-Hub-Signature-256` | `sha256= ` |\n\nManual verification:\n\n```elixir\n# WAHA\nExWaha.Webhooks.Signature.verify_sha512(raw_body, header_value, account.webhook_secret)\n\n# Meta\nExWaha.Webhooks.Signature.verify_meta_sha256(raw_body, header_value, account.app_secret)\n```\n\nComparison is constant-time via `:crypto.hash_equals/2`.","ref":"webhooks.html#hmac-signatures"},{"type":"extras","title":"WAHA event names - Webhooks","doc":"WAHA sends one event per HTTP POST. Common `event` values:\n\n- `message` — incoming message\n- `message.ack` — sent-message status update\n- `message.reaction` — emoji reaction added/removed\n- `session.status` — session transitioned (e.g. `WORKING → FAILED`)\n- `group.v2.join` / `group.v2.leave` / `group.v2.update`\n- `presence.update`\n\n`Event.from_waha/1` maps these to `kind`. Anything unrecognized lands as\n`:unknown` with the original payload in `raw`.","ref":"webhooks.html#waha-event-names"},{"type":"extras","title":"Meta event payloads - Webhooks","doc":"Meta posts an envelope with multiple entries → changes → values. ExWaha\nflattens to a list of `%Event{}` structs. A single POST commonly contains\nboth inbound `messages` and outbound `statuses` for previously-sent\nmessages.","ref":"webhooks.html#meta-event-payloads"},{"type":"extras","title":"Configuring webhooks - Webhooks","doc":"WAHA session config (passed to `ExWaha.Api.Sessions.create/2`):\n\n```elixir\nExWaha.Api.Sessions.create(account, %{\n  webhooks: [\n    %{\n      url: \"https://api.example.com/webhooks/waha/profile_42\",\n      events: [\"message\", \"message.ack\", \"session.status\"],\n      hmac: %{key: account.webhook_secret}\n    }\n  ]\n})\n```\n\nMeta webhooks are configured in the App Dashboard, not via API.","ref":"webhooks.html#configuring-webhooks"},{"type":"extras","title":"Providers","doc":"# Providers\n\n`:ex_waha` ships two providers behind one API:\n\n| | WAHA | Meta Cloud API |\n|---|---|---|\n| Hosted by | You (Docker) | Meta |\n| Underlying transport | WhatsApp Web reverse-engineered | Official Meta Graph API |\n| Cost | Server costs only | Per-conversation pricing |\n| Onboarding | Scan QR with any WhatsApp number | Approved business + WhatsApp Business Account (WABA) |\n| Free-form messaging | Always | Inside 24-hour customer service window only |\n| Templates | Not really | Required outside the 24h window |\n| Ban risk | **High** if abused | Low (they enforce instead) |\n| Webhook signature | HMAC-SHA512 | HMAC-SHA256 (`X-Hub-Signature-256`) |\n\nPick WAHA for prototypes, low-volume internal use, or markets where\nBusiness API onboarding is impractical. Pick Meta for production at scale.","ref":"providers.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Account structs - Providers","doc":"Both implement `ExWaha.Provider`. The facade dispatches by inspecting the\nstruct's module:\n\n```elixir\n# WAHA\naccount = ExWaha.Providers.Waha.Account.new(\n  ExWaha.Instance.new(base_url: \"...\", api_key: \"...\"),\n  \"profile_42\",\n  webhook_secret: \"shhh\"\n)\n\n# Meta\naccount = ExWaha.Providers.Meta.Account.new(\n  phone_number_id: \"123\",\n  access_token:    \"EAAB...\",\n  app_secret:      \"app_secret\",\n  business_account_id: \"456\",     # optional\n  api_version:     \"v22.0\"        # default\n)\n```\n\nSame call sites:\n\n```elixir\nExWaha.send_text(account, recipient, \"hi\")\nExWaha.send_media(account, recipient, %{type: :image, file: %{url: \"...\"}})\nExWaha.send_template(account, recipient, \"hello_world\", language: \"en_US\")\n```","ref":"providers.html#account-structs"},{"type":"extras","title":"Send-text behavior - Providers","doc":"| | WAHA | Meta |\n|---|---|---|\n| Endpoint | `POST /api/sendText` | `POST / /messages` |\n| Body | `{chatId, text, session}` | `{messaging_product: \"whatsapp\", to, type: \"text\", text: %{body}}` |\n| Recipient format | ` @c.us` | E.164 digits (no `+`) |\n| 24h window | N/A | Free-form only inside the window |","ref":"providers.html#send-text-behavior"},{"type":"extras","title":"Templates (Meta only) - Providers","doc":"Outside the 24-hour customer service window, Meta requires a pre-approved\ntemplate. WAHA returns `{:error, %Error{reason: :forbidden}}` if you call\n`send_template/4` against it.\n\n```elixir\nExWaha.send_template(meta_account, recipient, \"order_shipped\",\n  language: \"en_US\",\n  components: [\n    %{\n      type: \"body\",\n      parameters: [\n        %{type: \"text\", text: \"Mohammed\"},\n        %{type: \"text\", text: \"TRACK-12345\"}\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n)\n```","ref":"providers.html#templates-meta-only"},{"type":"extras","title":"Implementing a custom provider - Providers","doc":"`ExWaha.Provider` is the contract. To wrap a third backend (e.g. Twilio\nWhatsApp), implement:\n\n```elixir\ndefmodule MyApp.Providers.Twilio do\n  @behaviour ExWaha.Provider\n\n  defmodule Account do\n    defstruct [:account_sid, :auth_token, :from]\n  end\n\n  @impl true\n  def send_text(account, recipient, text, _opts), do: # ...\n  @impl true\n  def send_media(account, recipient, media, _opts), do: # ...\n  @impl true\n  def send_template(_account, _recipient, _template, _opts), do:\n    {:error, ExWaha.Error.exception(reason: :forbidden, message: \"no templates\")}\n  @impl true\n  def verify_signature(account, body, headers), do: # ...\n  @impl true\n  def parse_event(account, payload), do: # ...\nend\n```\n\nThen register it in `ExWaha.Provider.provider_for!/1` (or fork the dispatch\nto a config-based lookup).","ref":"providers.html#implementing-a-custom-provider"},{"type":"extras","title":"Switching providers per tenant - Providers","doc":"Because the account *is* the dispatch key, you can run different tenants on\ndifferent providers. A premium tenant on Meta, a low-volume tenant on WAHA,\nall in the same Phoenix app:\n\n```elixir\ndef account_for!(profile_id) do\n  case profile_tier(profile_id) do\n    :premium -> meta_account_for!(profile_id)\n    :basic   -> waha_account_for!(profile_id)\n  end\nend\n```\n\nThe rest of your code doesn't care.","ref":"providers.html#switching-providers-per-tenant"},{"type":"extras","title":"Telemetry events","doc":"# Telemetry events\n\nEvery outbound HTTP call is wrapped in a `:telemetry.span/3`, plus discrete\nevents for rate-limit decisions and session status changes.","ref":"telemetry.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Subscribing - Telemetry events","doc":"```elixir\n:telemetry.attach_many(\n  \"ex-waha\",\n  [\n    [:ex_waha, :request, :start],\n    [:ex_waha, :request, :stop],\n    [:ex_waha, :request, :exception],\n    [:ex_waha, :rate_limit, :throttled],\n    [:ex_waha, :rate_limit, :jitter],\n    [:ex_waha, :session, :status_changed],\n    [:ex_waha, :webhook, :received]\n  ],\n  &MyApp.Telemetry.handle/4,\n  nil\n)\n```","ref":"telemetry.html#subscribing"},{"type":"extras","title":"Event reference - Telemetry events","doc":"### `[:ex_waha, :request, :start]` / `:stop` / `:exception`\n\nStandard `:telemetry.span` events around every provider HTTP call.\n\n**Measurements** (on `:stop`):\n- `:duration` (native time units)\n\n**Metadata**:\n- `:provider` — `:waha` or `:meta`\n- `:method` — HTTP verb (WAHA only)\n- `:path` — URL path (WAHA only)\n- `:op` — `:send_text \\| :send_media \\| :send_template \\| :send_location \\| ...`\n- `:ok?` (on `:stop`) — `true` if the call returned `{:ok, _}`\n\n### `[:ex_waha, :rate_limit, :throttled]`\n\nEmitted when `Session.Server.gated_call/2` refuses a call because the token\nbucket is empty.\n\n**Measurements**: `%{wait_ms: integer}` — how long until a token is\nexpected to be available.\n**Metadata**: `%{}`\n\n### `[:ex_waha, :rate_limit, :jitter]`\n\nEmitted when `SafeSend.sleep_jitter/1` pauses before dispatching the\nunderlying call.\n\n**Measurements**: `%{ms: integer}`\n**Metadata**: `%{}`\n\n### `[:ex_waha, :session, :status_changed]`\n\nEmitted by `Session.Server` when the session's status atom changes.\n\n**Measurements**: `%{}`\n**Metadata**:\n- `:from` — previous status atom\n- `:to` — new status atom\n- `:account` — registry key tuple (e.g. `{:waha, base_url, session}`)\n\n### `[:ex_waha, :webhook, :received]`\n\nEmitted by `Webhooks.Handler.dispatch/3` for each event before invoking the\nhost handler.\n\n**Measurements**: `%{}`\n**Metadata**:\n- `:kind` — `Event.kind`\n- `:provider` — `:waha \\| :meta`","ref":"telemetry.html#event-reference"},{"type":"extras","title":"Example: prom_ex / Logger integration - Telemetry events","doc":"```elixir\ndefmodule MyApp.Telemetry do\n  require Logger\n\n  def handle([:ex_waha, :request, :stop], %{duration: dur}, %{op: op, ok?: ok?}, _) do\n    Logger.info(\"ex_waha #{op} #{ok? && \"ok\" || \"err\"} #{System.convert_time_unit(dur, :native, :millisecond)}ms\")\n  end\n\n  def handle([:ex_waha, :rate_limit, :throttled], %{wait_ms: ms}, _, _) do\n    Logger.warning(\"ex_waha rate limited — backoff #{ms}ms\")\n  end\n\n  def handle([:ex_waha, :session, :status_changed], _, %{from: from, to: to, account: acct}, _) do\n    Logger.info(\"ex_waha #{inspect(acct)} #{from} -> #{to}\")\n  end\n\n  def handle(_, _, _, _), do: :ok\nend\n```","ref":"telemetry.html#example-prom_ex-logger-integration"}],"proglang":"elixir","content_type":"text/markdown","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.40.1"}}